Ingredients:
Sugar, 1½C
Milk, ½C
Butter, 8 tbs
Unsweetened cocoa powder, ¼C
Rolled oats, 3C
Smooth peanut butter, 1C
Vanilla extract, 1 tbs
Salt, 1 pinch (omit if butter is salted)

Equipment:
Baking sheet
Saucepan
Stirring spoon
Table spoon


Line baking sheet with wax paper. Boil sugar, milk, butter, & cocoa in saucepan on medium heat for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients. Spoon onto baking sheet in dollops. Chill in fridge for 30 minutes. Serve cold and store in a refrigerated air tight container.
